LIBCDAYDIFF
===========

A portable, pure C library for date arithmetic, parsing, formatting, and
timezone-aware operations.

OVERVIEW
--------

libcdaydiff provides a comprehensive set of functions to work with dates and
date‑times in C. It handles:

  - Parsing dates from strings with automatic or explicit delimiters
  - Validation of dates including leap year rules
  - Date differences (days inclusive/exclusive and full year-month-day breakdown)
  - Date manipulation (add days, months, years)
  - Day‑of‑week, day‑of‑year, ISO week number calculations
  - Comparison (equals, before/after)
  - String formatting with strftime‑like specifiers
  - Timezone support: local, UTC, and arbitrary offset
  - Epoch (Unix time) conversion both UTC and local

The library is written in C99, has no external dependencies, and compiles on
any platform with a C compiler and standard library.

FEATURES
--------

  * Robust parsing – auto‑detects delimiter or accepts a custom delimiter set.
  * Full validation – checks day/month/year ranges, leap years.
  * Date difference – inclusive and exclusive day counts; full year/month/day
    breakdown.
  * Date arithmetic – add/subtract days, months, years with proper end‑of‑month
    pinning.
  * ISO week number – conforms to ISO 8601.
  * Flexible formatting – supports %Y, %m, %d, %B, %b, %A, %a, %H, %M, %S, %z,
    and %%.
  * Timezone handling – get current local/UTC DateTime, or arbitrary offset.
  * Epoch conversion – to/from Unix time (seconds since 1970‑01‑01).
  * Error reporting – every function returns a clear error code, with a
    human‑readable string available via date_error_string().
  * C++ compatible – header wrapped in extern "C".

GETTING STARTED
---------------

Prerequisites:
  - A C99 compiler (GCC, Clang, MSVC 2013+, etc.)
  - GNU Make (or compatible) for the provided Makefile
  - Standard POSIX tools (ar, install) for building and installing

Building from Source:

  git clone https://github.com/mroczect/libcdaydiff.git
  cd libcdaydiff
  make

This produces:
  - libcdaydiff.a   – static library

Object files are placed in the obj/ directory.

Available Make targets:

  all       Build the static library (default)
  clean     Remove all build artifacts (obj/ and libcdaydiff.a)
  install   Install the library and header to /usr/local

Override the compiler or flags:

  make CC=clang CFLAGS="-O3 -march=native"

Linking Against the Library:

After building, include the header and link with -lcdaydiff.

  #include <libcdaydiff.h>

  int main(void) {
      Date d;
      date_parse("01.01.2025", NULL, &d);
      // ...
      return 0;
  }

Compile and link:

  gcc -I/usr/local/include myapp.c -L/usr/local/lib -lcdaydiff -o myapp

USAGE
-----

The library is built as a static library. There is no standalone executable
included; the provided test.c acts as a comprehensive unit test suite.

To run the tests:

  make
  gcc -I src/include test.c libcdaydiff.a -o test
  ./test

All tests should pass if the library is functioning correctly.

API REFERENCE
-------------

Data Types

  Date        – struct { int day; int month; int year; }
  DateTime    – Date plus hour, minute, second, and tz_offset (minutes)
  DateDiff    – struct { int years; int months; int days; }
  DateError   – enum with error codes (DATE_OK, DATE_ERR_NULL_POINTER, etc.)

Core Validation

  int date_is_leap_year(int year);
  int date_days_in_month(int month, int year);
  int date_validate(int day, int month, int year);

Parsing

  int date_parse(const char *str, const char *delims, Date *out);

  If delims is NULL, the function auto‑detects the delimiter (first non‑digit
  character). Returns DATE_OK on success, DATE_ERR_PARSE if the format is
  invalid, or DATE_ERR_INVALID_DATE if the date does not exist.

Date Difference

  int date_diff_days(const Date *d1, const Date *d2, int64_t *result);
      – Inclusive day count (same day returns 1).
  int date_diff_days_excl(const Date *d1, const Date *d2, int64_t *result);
      – Exclusive day count (same day returns 0).
  int date_diff_full(const Date *d1, const Date *d2, DateDiff *out);
      – Full year/month/day breakdown. d1 must be earlier than d2.

Manipulation

  int date_add_days(const Date *in, int64_t n, Date *out);
  int date_add_months(const Date *in, int n, Date *out);
  int date_add_years(const Date *in, int n, Date *out);

  All functions handle end‑of‑month pinning (e.g., 31 Jan + 1 month → 28/29 Feb).

Information

  int date_day_of_week(const Date *d);   // 0=Sunday … 6=Saturday
  int date_day_of_year(const Date *d);
  int date_week_number_iso(const Date *d);

Comparison

  int date_compare(const Date *d1, const Date *d2);  // -1, 0, 1
  int date_equals(const Date *d1, const Date *d2);   // 1 if equal

Current Time

  int date_now(Date *out);
  int date_now_utc(Date *out);
  int datetime_now(DateTime *out);
  int datetime_now_utc(DateTime *out);
  int datetime_now_tz(DateTime *out, int offset_minutes);

Formatting

  int date_format(const Date *d, const char *fmt, char *buf, size_t bufsize);
  int datetime_format(const DateTime *dt, const char *fmt, char *buf,
                      size_t bufsize);

  Format specifiers:
    %Y – 4‑digit year, %m – 2‑digit month, %d – 2‑digit day
    %B – full month name, %b – abbreviated month
    %A – full weekday name, %a – abbreviated weekday
    %H – hour (00‑23), %M – minute, %S – second
    %z – timezone offset (±HHMM)
    %% – literal '%'

Epoch Conversion

  int date_to_epoch_utc(const Date *d, int64_t *epoch_secs);
  int date_from_epoch_utc(int64_t epoch_secs, Date *out);
  int date_to_epoch_local(const Date *d, int64_t *epoch_secs);
  int date_from_epoch_local(int64_t epoch_secs, Date *out);

Error Handling

  const char *date_error_string(DateError err);

  Returns a static string describing the error code.

PROJECT STRUCTURE
-----------------

  libcdaydiff/
  ├── src/
  │   ├── include/
  │   │   └── libcdaydiff.h          # Public API header
  │   ├── internal/
  │   │   └── libcdaydiff_internal.h # Internal helpers
  │   ├── core.c                     # Validation, leap year, epoch helpers
  │   ├── parser.c                   # String-to-Date parsing
  │   ├── diff.c                     # Date difference functions
  │   ├── manip.c                    # Date arithmetic
  │   ├── info.c                     # Day‑of‑week, day‑of‑year, ISO week
  │   ├── comparison.c               # date_compare, date_equals
  │   ├── fmt.c                      # date_format, datetime_format
  │   ├── epoch.c                    # Epoch conversion
  │   ├── tz.c                       # Timezone and current time
  │   └── error.c                    # Error string mapping
  ├── test.c                         # Unit test suite
  ├── Makefile                       # Build automation
  ├── LICENSE
  └── README

